Citation.sTitle: Relative Permittivity and Apparent Dipole Moments of Nitromethane, Nitroethane, 1-Nitropropane and 2- Nitropropane in Several Nonpolar Solvents.
Citation.sAbstract: The relative permittivity and apparent dipole moments of (nitromethane + benzene or + tetrachloromethane) at 298.15 K and 318.15 K, and (nitroethane + tetrachloromethane or + cyclohexane or + 1,4-dimethylbenzene), (1-nitropropane + tetrachloromethane or + cyclohexane or + 1,4 dimethylbenzene) and (2-nitropropane + tetrachloromethane or + cyclohexane or + 1,4-dimethylbenzene or + 2,3-dimethylbenzene) at 298.15 K were measured to mole fractions of the nitroalkanes of 0.09. Measurements were made using a stepwise dilution technique with a two-terminal dielectric cell. The apparent dipole moments were calculated using the Frohlich equation.
